<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="647" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">561.311F1/204: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-30T18:00:00-04:00">August 30,
                                1933—6 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>231. For Murphy from Wallace. Congratulations on your great achievement. This
                        is the momentous step.</p>
                    <p>You have not yet sent us appendix A or appendix B referred to in text of the
                        general agreement. Please send these to us by cable. If too lengthy to
                        summarize please be sure that full copies are mailed to the Department or
                        bring with you on your return. We are assuming that any further details
                        concerning interpretation of fulfillment of agreement will be taken up
                        through the Advisory Committee. [Wallace.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
            </body></text></TEI>